description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen for a Physiotherapist work within the Children’s Physiotherapy Service at Wirral University Teaching Hospital and within the community settings covered by the trust. The post holder will be based within the Community services in a variety of settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have post graduate experience of working with Children and be familiar and confident with assessment and treatment of a full range of conditions associated with children and young persons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will require the skills and experience necessary to support the team at Band 6 level&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent support is available from an experienced team leader via robust supervision. The successful candidate will also have the opportunity to participate in the ongoing development of the teams and will be encouraged to undertake audit projects and help promote the service to the wider MDT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will also demonstrate:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of Children’s Practice at undergraduate / post graduate level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the ability to problem solve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;appropriate prioritisation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;good team working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane Fieldhouse Ext 6552 or 0151 514 2525&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;janefieldhouse@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
